data.Description: Asses This subclass is defined through the following headings/subheadings of the HS 2007: 0101.30.

Buffalo This subclass includes: -  buffalo, species of Bubalus, mainly bubalus, ami, depressicornis, nanus (buffalo, Indian buffalo, water buffalo, carabao, and Pigmi buffalo) - caffers, African buffalo, species of Syncerus -  bisons, species of Bison, American and European This subclass does not include: - cattle, species of Bos, mainly bovis, taurus, indicus, grunniens, gaurus, grontalis and sondaicus, cf. 02111

Bactrian camel (Camelus bactrianus); Arabian camel (C. dromedarius)  Animals of the genus listed, regardless of age, sex, or purpose raised. Data are expressed in number of heads. (Unofficial definition)

Common ox (Bos taurus); zebu, humped ox (Bos indicus); Asiatic ox (subgenus Bibos); Tibetan yak (Poephagus grunniens). Animals of the genus listed, that are producing milk in commercial quantities for human consumption.

Common ox (Bos taurus); zebu, humped ox (Bos indicus); Asiatic ox (subgenus Bibos); Tibetan yak (Poephagus grunniens). Animals of the genus listed, that are produce calves for meat or to provide draft power.
Ducks This subclass includes: - ducks, species of Anas , mainlyplatyrhynchos
Goats This subclass is defined through the following headings/subheadings of the HS 2007: 0104.20.
Horses This subclass is defined through the following headings/subheadings of the HS 2007: 0101.21, .29.
Mules and hinnies This subclass is defined through the following headings/subheadings of the HS 2007: 0101.90.
Sheep This subclass is defined through the following headings/subheadings of the HS 2007: 0104.10.
Turkeys This subclass includes: - common and ocellated turkeys, Meleagris gallopavo
